# ledgers/example-project.axls

@META
id: dynovo-agent-rules-project
v: 0.2
kind: axls
modified: @20260708
owner: alex
ruleset: ../rules/base.axlr
purpose: durable project-level state for AXL rule development

@STATE
status: ACTIVE
project: dynovo-agent-rules
focus: Agent eXecution Language for compact coding-agent rules
repo: :https://github.com/squoyster/dynovo-agent-rules
default_router: AGENTS.md
default_rules: rules/base.axlr
full_spec: axl/spec.axlr

@GOALS
g001: ACTIVE | compress agent behavioral instructions without losing normative force
g002: ACTIVE | separate execution rules from mutable state ledgers
g003: ACTIVE | support Hermes/OpenCode/Codex-style coding agents
g004: ACTIVE | keep default-load context small
g005: ACTIVE | load domain overlays only when task-relevant

@ARCH
a001: AXL-R | .axlr | immutable/mostly-static execution rules
a002: AXL-S | .axls | mutable durable state, plans, logs, handoffs
a003: AXL-P | .axlp | sparse patch/update files
a004: AXL-T | .axlt | shared symbols, sigils, status enums

@FILES
f001: AGENTS.md | small router; default entrypoint for agents
f002: rules/base.axlr | default operational rules
f003: axl/spec.axlr | full AXL-R language spec
f004: axl/types.axlt | shared syntax/operators/status values
f005: axl/state-spec.axls | durable state/ledger rules
f006: axl/patch-spec.axlp | sparse update format
f007: ledgers/example-task.axls | task-level ledger example
f008: ledgers/example-project.axls | project-level ledger example

@PIN
p001: AXL means squoyster Agent eXecution Language.
p002: Do not confuse with Igazine Agent eXchange Language.
p003: Borrow file discipline/state mechanics, not purpose.
p004: Keep rules and ledgers separate.
p005: Never load the full spec for routine work unless needed.

@DECISIONS
d001: DONE | split AXL into AXL-R and AXL-S
d002: DONE | keep AGENTS.md as markdown router for compatibility
d003: DONE | use .axlr/.axls/.axlp/.axlt extensions
d004: OPEN | decide whether Hermes should auto-load local clone or GitHub raw URLs
d005: OPEN | decide whether memory files should be .md, .axls, or both

@RISKS
r001: MED | symbolic notation may be misread by smaller models unless notation block is loaded
r002: MED | too many overlays can recreate context bloat
r003: LOW | nonstandard extensions may need editor/tooling support
r004: MED | agents may mutate append-only logs unless state rules are explicit

@NEXT
n001: DONE | create axl/types.axlt
n002: DONE | convert rules/base.md to rules/base.axlr
n003: DONE | create axl/state-spec.axls
n004: DONE | create axl/patch-spec.axlp
n005: DONE | update AGENTS.md router to reference new files
n006: TODO | add Hermes SOUL.md pointer example
n007: TODO | fill domain overlays (git/verification/security/aws/node-react/postgres/java-spring)

